Private Sub cbGrpDesc_AfterUpdate()
  On Error GoTo SubError
    Select Case Me.cbGrpDesc.Value
     Case "Junior Division"
       Me.G_Div = "J"
     Case "Senior Division"
       Me.G_Div = "S"
     Case "Junior or Senior Division"
       Me.G_Div = Null
     Case Else  ' user entered something not in the dropdown box
        Dim test As String
        test = Mid(Me.cbGrpDesc.Value, 1, 15) ' rev 5.3.2  Just test the first 15 characters to see if
        ' is junior or senior.  G_Div is used to determine the default script (unless award is Combined Assy)
        Select Case test
          Case "Junior Division"  ' for junior and senior as first 15 characters, set to J or S
           Me.G_Div = "J"
          Case "Senior Division"
           Me.G_Div = "S"
          Case Else
           Me.G_Div = Null
        End Select
        '  Allways give the message
        MsgBox "Warning: Using Groups other than those listed is not recommended but possible!" & vbCrLf & _
             " Be Sure to set G_Div to 'J' or 'S' (The default Script Assembly section.)" & vbCrLf & _
             " See 'Script Sorting' in Help for details."
    End Select
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox Err.Description

End Sub
